 of modernity in the first half of the twentieth century. She draws on a vast and unusual range of sources to stitch together a rich patchwork quilt of vivid stories and unforgettable characters, revealing how Soho became a showcase for a new cosmopolitan identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCity and town lifezEnglandzLondonxHistoryy20th century. 0aCosmopolitanismzEnglandzLondonxHistoryy20th century. 0aCultural pluralismzEnglandzLondonxHistoryy20th century. 0aNightlifezEnglandzLondonxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical culturezEnglandzLondonxHistoryy20th century. 0aPopular culturezEnglandzLondonxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial changezEnglandzLondonxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300183689423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300183689.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles